The course provides an overview of the methodology of teaching Estonian as a second language. Topics covered include learning and teaching styles and methods, lesson and syllabus development, grammar, vocabulary and Estonian skills development, assessment and feedback, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  1) to introduce the basic knowledge of the methodology of teaching Estonian as a second language 2) to provide students with an overview of the curriculum, the syllabus and the preparation of the teacher's work plan, the planning and targeting of lessons and the testing, assessment and feedback of teaching Estonian as a second language.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon competing the course, the student: 1) Is aware of bilingual education programs in use in Estonia. 2) Will be able to analyze learning materials developed for learning Estonian as a second language. 3) Is able to prepare assignments for the development of basic skills and language skills for learning Estonian as a second language / foreign language. 4) Is able to analyze and produce text-based study materials in the Estonian language class. 5) Can plan lesson and assessment based on study material
